<h3>2. Master the Controls</h3>
<ul>
 	<li><strong>WASD</strong>: Move your character around the map.</li>
 	<li><strong>Mouse</strong>: Look around and interact with objects.</li>
 	<li><strong>F</strong>: Use your flashlight to navigate dark areas.</li>
 	<li><strong>Left Control</strong>: Crouch to hide from enemies.</li>
 	<li><strong>Tab</strong>: Access your wristwatch to check the time.</li>
 	<li><strong>Left Shift</strong>: Sprint to quickly escape animatronics.</li>
 	<li><strong>E</strong>: Exit the car at the beginning of the game.</li>
 	<li><strong>Escape</strong>: Access the pause menu.</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div class="skill-steps">
<h3>3. Surviving the Nights</h3>
<ul>
 	<li><strong>Monitor Animatronics</strong>: Keep a close watch on the cameras and audio to track <em>Springtrap</em>’s movements. He will often use the vents to sneak closer, so be prepared to lock them at any time.</li>
 	<li><strong>Avoid Phantoms</strong>: Phantom animatronics like <em>Phantom Freddy</em> and <em>Phantom Chica</em> will try to distract you. These hallucinations don't kill you directly, but they can disable your systems, leaving you vulnerable.</li>
 	<li><strong>Use Audio Cues</strong>: Pay attention to sound cues to anticipate where <em>Springtrap</em> is. The creepy ambient noise gets louder as he gets closer.</li>
</ul>
</div>
