<div class="features-section">
<div class="features-grid">
<div class="feature-item">
<h3>A New Layer of Horror</h3>
<div class="description-section">In "FNAF 3: The Mind of a Killer," you are thrown into the twisted world of <em>Fazbear's Fright: The Horror Attraction</em>. As a security guard, your role is to survive five terrifying nights against <em>Springtrap</em>, the infamous animatronic haunted by the soul of William Afton, the killer from the FNAF lore. The game enhances the classic <em>FNAF 3</em> experience by incorporating an engaging free-roam mode, adding a whole new level of tension as players explore every corner of the haunted attraction.</div>
</div>
<div class="feature-item">
<h3>The Thrill of Free-Roam Gameplay</h3>
<div class="description-section">While many FNAF fan games follow the traditional point-and-click mechanics, "The Mind of a Killer" stands out by offering players a free-roam experience within the terrifying confines of the attraction. You’re not just stuck in a security office — you have the freedom to explore the entire environment. However, this freedom comes with a price: <em>Springtrap</em> and the other phantoms are lurking in the shadows, waiting to strike.</div>
</div>
<div class="feature-item">
<h3>A Dark and Gripping Storyline</h3>
<div class="description-section">Pain and terror dominate the narrative of "The Mind of a Killer." As the protagonist, you are haunted by nightmares and plagued by visions that blur the lines between reality and the supernatural. The game kicks off with a jarring nightmare sequence where springlocks pierce your skin, forcing you to confront the horrific memories tied to <em>Fazbear’s Fright</em>. The moment you wake up in your car, the terror begins, and you quickly realize that something is deeply wrong with the attraction you’ve been hired to guard.</div>
</div>
<div class="feature-item">
<h3>Secrets, Easter Eggs, and Lore</h3>
<div class="description-section">One of the most exciting aspects of "FNAF 3: The Mind of a Killer" is the abundance of hidden secrets and Easter eggs scattered throughout the game. From creepy minigames on the arcade machines to strange visual glitches that hint at deeper mysteries, players are encouraged to search every corner of the map.</div>
</div>
<div class="feature-item">
<h3>Animatronics and Threats</h3>
<div class="description-section">The animatronics in "The Mind of a Killer" are a deadly force, led by the relentless <em>Springtrap</em>. But he's not the only one you need to worry about. Phantom versions of <em>Freddy</em>, <em>Chica</em>, <em>Foxy</em>, and even <em>Mangle</em> lurk in the attraction, each with their own mechanics and strategies for survival. The phantoms are relentless, and their presence heightens the tension as they appear unpredictably throughout your shift.</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>

